).

Atrial (vestibular) sense organ short with densely arranged slender papillae (diam. 
7-10 µm
), basally united in groups of up to four. “Horseshoe-shaped” ciliary tract incomplete: it begins unpaired at midpoint of organ extension and then runs pairedly posterio-ventrally to end of the common atriobuccal opening; ventral tracts patchy, anteriorly missing.

Dorso-terminal sense organ prominent at dorsal end of body (behind end of mantle cavity; 
Fig. 7
).

